  "texts": [
    "Further, graph-based approaches such as GraphRAG offer significant improvements by extracting knowledge graphs and structuring them hierarchically to improve RAG-based tasks (Edge et al. 2024).",
    "GraphRAG can be used to extract a knowledge graph from text, building a hierarchy that is then used to leverage these graph-based structures to perform a RAG-based task.",
    "In addition, retrieval-augmented thoughts (RAT) enhance augmentation through a zero-shot Chain of Thought (CoT), iteratively refining it with retrieved information.",
    "This method provides more contextual and coherent output, supporting tasks such as code generation and mathematical reasoning (Wang et al. 2024c).",
    "The underlying mechanism, CoT, which has become critical to improving LLM reasoning capabilities, was first developed by Google in 2022 (Wei et al. 2022) and has now been integrated into models such as GPT-4o."
  ],
